    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the sudden shift in tone and the excessive goblin references! I can certainly explain the escrow process clearly and professionally without the fantasy elements.\n\nAn **escrow account** is a neutral third-party service (like a title company or an attorney) that holds funds and documents during a real estate transaction. Its primary purpose is to ensure that all conditions of the sale are met before the money changes hands and the title transfers.\n\nIn the context of buying a home in Toronto, the escrow agent acts as a neutral referee between you, the seller, and the lender. They manage the timeline to ensure that the seller's mortgage is paid off, the property taxes are updated, and the title is clear before releasing the purchase money to the seller. This protects you from receiving a house with legal issues or liens, and it protects the seller from receiving their funds until you have taken possession of the property.\n\nEssentially, escrow provides a secure, regulated framework for the closing process, ensuring that both parties can trust the transaction will be completed fairly and according to the contract.",
