      "content": "The escrow agent acts as the ultimate neutral referee, holding the funds in a secure vault until every single condition of the contract is met. If the seller tries to pull something or there is a dispute about the funds, the escrow agent simply freezes the transaction and refuses to release any money until the issue is resolved. They do not take sides; they just follow the contract like a very strict, very literal goblin who refuses to move a single pebble until the path is clear.\n\nIf the seller refuses to clear the title or pay off liens, the escrow agent will notify the buyer and potentially the lender, effectively halting the closing. This prevents the buyer from ever getting the keys to a house that isn't legally theirs. In the worst-case scenario, if the seller disappears or becomes uncooperative, the escrow agent can sometimes assist in filing a claim or working with the court to resolve the dispute, ensuring the buyer doesn't end up with a \"goblin-occupied\" property that has no clear ownership.\n\nThe process is designed to be airtight: if there is a conflict, the deal stops. No one gets paid, no one gets the house, and the dispute is sent back to the drawing board",
